		"abstract": "Presents an obituary of Gary Gygax (1938-2008). Gary Gygax was the son of Martin, an immigrant from Switzerland, and an American mother. In recent times, this would be a perfect combination for a future president of the United States. He started his game designer's career at Guidon Games in 1970, then founded Tactical Studies Rules (TSR) in 1973. As president of the Dungeons & Dragons Entertainment Corporation, he coproduced the animated television show. Despite serious heart disease, he was still active in the gaming world, hosting D&D sessions at his home in Lake Geneva, Wisconsin, and corresponding with gaming enthusiasts from everywhere. He will be missed, especially by those readers who may not have ever heard of him. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2016 APA, all rights reserved)",
