		"type": "chapter",
		"abstract": "This chapter describes the development of a theory of role-playing games at the Forge, discussing its initial focus on ‘GNS,’ the three ‘aesthetic priorities’ of Gamism, Narrativism, and Simulationism that were held to inform TRPG design and play. It describes some of the arguments about GNS that were raised, and describes how GNS fits into the broader ‘Big Model’ of Forge theory as ‘Creative Agenda’ (CA) that functioned as potential orienting principles for a given play group. It presents the Big Model as a kind of frame-analytic approach to understanding the structure of TRPG activity, and suggests that within such an approach, CA serve the useful purpose of allowing that activity to be understood as play. It also discusses the experience of Forge participants in grappling with the Big Model.",
