		"type": "article-journal",
		"abstract": "Describes how art therapy helped a 14-yr-old male deal with his diabetes and emotional and behavioral difficulties. The art therapy process provided the patient with an outlet for his anger and depression through the art media. Through problem-solving skills and decision making during the sessions, the patient gained a sense of mastery and control within his limited and restricted environment. It is suggested that art therapy serves as a creative tool in which adolescents can express feelings and issues crucial to their recovery. The art process further aids adolescents in developing their sense of identity and self-esteem, as well as preserving their autonomy by giving them a sense of mastery and control. It is concluded that both the therapist and patient need to work together to promote healing and growth. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2016 APA, all rights reserved)",
