		"abstract": "This work has the objective to present a combat simulator model to D&D players that considers the possibility of actions formalized in game rules added with players’ capability to acquire strategies that will guide them to improve their performance during game simulations. The quality improvement of the strategy adopted by the player with the proposed model, called Adaptive, is evidenced through combat simulations between a team with and without the ability to acquire information, or different levels of this ability, considering that each player can have different levels of experience. It was noticed that the ability to acquire trustworthy information can make the player’s strategy improve exponentially depending on the rate of information acquirement.",
